Bug 2049110 - Make nsIMsgFolder.firstNewMessage infallible. r=mkmelin

Previously, accessing firstNewMessage would throw NS_ERROR_ILLEGAL_VALUE when
there were no new messages in the folder, requiring callers to guard with
hasNewMessages or wrap in try-catch. This threw confusing errors into the
console, particularly when clicking a new mail notification on a folder
whose in-memory mNewMessages flag had fallen out of sync with the database.

GetFirstNewMessage now returns nullptr with NS_OK when:
- There is no database open
- The database has no new messages (key == nsMsgKey_None)
- The key doesn't resolve to a valid message header

The IDL documentation is updated to match.

JS callers are simplified:
- onMessagesLoaded in mailCommon.js now just null-checks firstNewMessage
  instead of using try-catch.
- selectMessage in about3Pane.js now clears scrollToNewMessage before the
  async folder load, preventing onMessagesLoaded from later scrolling the
  user away from the message they clicked on in a notification.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311486


